"title": "4007: creation, and God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4007: creation, and god",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The natural world is sustained by God and speaks of God.</p>\n<h2>God sustains the creation</h2>\n<h3>He upholds the natural order</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:33-Job38:37\">JOB 38:33–38:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:1-Ps104:35\">PSA 104:1–104:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:6-Ps135:7\">PSA 135:6–135:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:16-Ps145:17\">PSA 145:16–145:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:29-Matt10:30\">MAT 10:29–10:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:17\">COL 1:17</a></p>\n<h3>He sustains humanity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:28\">ACT 17:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:4\">JOB 33:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps36:6\">PSA 36:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:34-Dan4:35\">DAN 4:34–4:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:6\">1CO 8:6</a></p>\n<h3>Creation is upheld for the good of humanity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:22\">GEN 8:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:12-Gen9:16\">GEN 9:12–9:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:11\">MAT 6:11</a></p>\n<h3>God's sustaining power reserves the world for judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:7\">2PE 3:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:9-2Pet3:12\">2PE 3:9–3:12</a> <em>Time is being given for sinners to repent.</em></p>\n<h2>God has given humanity responsibility to preserve creation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:28\">GEN 1:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:15\">GEN 2:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:1-Gen9:3\">GEN 9:1–9:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:6-Ps8:8\">PSA 8:6–8:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:16\">PSA 115:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:8\">HEB 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:7\">JAS 3:7</a></p>\n<h2>Creation is spoilt by sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:17-Gen3:19\">GEN 3:17–3:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:20-Rom8:22\">ROM 8:20–8:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:8\">HEB 6:8</a></p>\n<h2>Creation speaks of God's nature and character</h2>\n<h3>His revelation of himself</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job12:7-Job12:10\">JOB 12:7–12:10</a></strong> <em>This is not to suggest that animals can talk to human beings, rather it is a poetic device to stress what can be learnt from created things.</em></p>\n<h3>His eternal power and divine nature</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:20\">ROM 1:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:17\">JER 32:17</a></p>\n<h3>His authority</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:4-Job39:30\">JOB 38:4–39:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:2\">JER 33:2</a></p>\n<h3>His glory and majesty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:1-Ps19:2\">PSA 19:1–19:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:1-Ps8:9\">PSA 8:1–8:9</a></p>\n<h3>His love and faithfulness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps36:5\">PSA 36:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:30\">MAT 6:30</a></p>\n<h3>His power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:25-Isa40:28\">ISA 40:25–40:28</a></strong></p>\n<h3>His wisdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps136:5\">PSA 136:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:27-Prov8:29\">PRO 8:27–8:29</a></p>\n<h3>His unchangeableness and eternity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:25-Ps102:27\">PSA 102:25–102:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:1-Ps90:2\">PSA 90:1–90:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:11\">HEB 1:11</a></p>\n<h3>His spiritual work in believers' lives</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:3-Matt13:43\">MAT 13:3–13:43</a></p>",
